  <summary>4/9/2003--Introduced.
Amends the Immigration and Nationality Act, with respect to the granting of posthumous citizenship to a member of the armed forces who died from an active service-related injury or disease incurred during a period of military hostilities, to eliminate the prohibition on the provision of, and provide immigration status benefits to, the surviving spouse and children of such person.Makes the provisions of this Act applicable to grants of posthumous citizenship after September 11, 2001.</summary>
